China reiterated its "one country, two systems" approach to Taiwan while unveiling its anti-secession law.
MAC Deputy Chairman Chiu Tai-shan criticized Beijing's provocative move to legalize a military invasion of Taiwan.
President Chen Shui-bian condemned the proposed law as a threat to regional stability.
Mainland China's push for the law drew opposition from the US and EU.
Taiwan may hold a referendum on unification terms if Beijing enforces the law.
The Legislative Yuan plans to denounce Beijing's legislation.
Overall, tensions rise as Taiwan braces for potential conflict over the anti-secession law.
